{
  "stem": "13457.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And sure enough, within few-- it, it transpired that we spent the night in no man's land.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Within few hundred feet, somebody walks out from behind a bush with a gun in his hand, obviously a Russian soldier, and says to us in Russian-- my mother knew Russian, too-- [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], which means, turn around and go back where you came from.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because the Russians, whatever the Germans were letting the refugees out, the Germans were not-- the Russians were not letting in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So of course, everybody started crying.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it probably broke the heart of the Russian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He says, OK-- he saw a bunch of kids and wounded soldier and, and, and women, and took us to the station there, right by the border.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Well, by the border, that put us overnight.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Sure enough, there was one doctor there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My mother came to him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she told him that my father is a physician.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Turn out that the guy was a Jewish doctor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it-- he gave us big hunks of sugar to eat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And somehow he arranged that the next morning-- we still someplace spent few hours in a cottage of peasants there, slept in one bed, the, the whole family.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And, and there was no floor in the, in these cottages.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was only mud.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And anyway, we, we went-- we dried up a little bit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "First thing next morning, we took the train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we went to Rudna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we joined my father, my aunt, and my two cousins.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This is the Weinberg family, Franka.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And so the-- so-to-speak, there we are.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And that was, then, the very end of 1939.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Now that takes us to a segment of time between 1939, end of '39, to June, 1941, when the Germans invade Russia.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
